<hr local-id=3D"b24c898f485d">
<h2 local-id=3D"a11b7df362df" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-3.2UseC=
ases">3.2 Use Cases</h2>
<hr local-id=3D"f8056c0f8e61">
<h2 local-id=3D"54941416bcd1" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-3.2.1Us=
eCase1:ViewInfrastructureDashboard">3.2.1 Use Case 1: View Infrastructure D=
ashboard</h2>
<p local-id=3D"bd043a244980">Description<br>
The DevOps engineer accesses the CloudWatch dashboard to view the performan=
ce metrics of EC2 instances.</p>
<p local-id=3D"37237f0e040b">Actors<br>
DevOps Engineer</p>
<p local-id=3D"afa650d33412">Preconditions</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3f623b5eae54">
<li local-id=3D"edaa892b5f31">
<p local-id=3D"5ef074230422">EC2 instances are running</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"01fac2dfa93a">
<p local-id=3D"a9ba085e4102">CloudWatch dashboard is created</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"22c47edc06c9">
<p local-id=3D"47cbec21e624">Metrics are being collected</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"93edffb34f35">Postconditions</p>
<ul local-id=3D"64137a57ab73">
<li local-id=3D"058a1495cdc3">
<p local-id=3D"f37f2fa43ab7">Infrastructure performance metrics are display=
ed on the dashboard</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"bbc84be668a8">Flow of Events</p>
<p local-id=3D"ac793ce902a3">Step 1<br>
DevOps engineer logs into AWS Management Console.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f49cbd112220">Step 2<br>
The engineer navigates to the CloudWatch service.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5912d56ea0c7">Step 3<br>
The engineer opens the EC2 monitoring dashboard.</p>
<p local-id=3D"bd021ebe7705">Step 4<br>
The dashboard displays metrics for CPU, memory, disk usage, and network act=
ivity.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a5100dc54948">Alternative Flow</p>
<p local-id=3D"c1282a93a4a3">If an instance is not sending metrics, the das=
hboard may show missing or incomplete data.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"c79ac90490a5">
<h2 local-id=3D"daf63bc88c66" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-3.2.2Us=
eCase2:MonitorEC2Performance">3.2.2 Use Case 2: Monitor EC2 Performance</h2=
>
<p local-id=3D"2780f54c5c59">Description<br>
The operations team monitors performance metrics to detect system issues.</=
p>
<p local-id=3D"830964ad9173">Actors<br>
Operations Team</p>
<p local-id=3D"8c7539a61c24">Preconditions</p>
<ul local-id=3D"5c4a9675bdde">
<li local-id=3D"1ebe20244f65">
<p local-id=3D"55019bc95ab7">Monitoring metrics are available</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6e4c1285b5c4">
<p local-id=3D"aa47217e5450">EC2 instances are operational</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"91df94e71727">Postconditions</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6b13e56f29ae">
<li local-id=3D"58c988082cfd">
<p local-id=3D"189fad1d0fdd">The team identifies performance trends or anom=
alies</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"aac40c7523cb">Flow of Events</p>
<p local-id=3D"d71fe325e78d">Step 1<br>
The operations team accesses the monitoring dashboard.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7880fbc7fed5">Step 2<br>
The team reviews CPU utilization graphs.</p>
<p local-id=3D"93326e3222a8">Step 3<br>
The team reviews memory and disk usage statistics.</p>
<p local-id=3D"80b33ccc186f">Step 4<br>
Network activity graphs are analyzed.</p>
<p local-id=3D"43b58265f273">Step 5<br>
The team identifies any unusual spikes or performance issues.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1470eae8a1d6">Alternative Flow</p>
<p local-id=3D"9ee5a98d863a">If abnormal metrics are detected, further inve=
stigation may be required.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"eaf01c12bb46">
<h1 local-id=3D"1d690c83ce3e" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-4.Non-F=
unctionalRequirements">4. Non-Functional Requirements</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"12badef5d966" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-4.1Perf=
ormanceRequirements">4.1 Performance Requirements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"362e8b9b5d93">The dashboard should load within <strong>2=E2=
=80=933 seconds</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c09098ff0108">Metrics should refresh automatically at regula=
r intervals to reflect real-time system performance.</p>
<p local-id=3D"460a5f1f2729">The system should support monitoring multiple =
EC2 instances simultaneously.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"2bc46d7d4546">
<h2 local-id=3D"5f8dd7f6fe43" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-4.2Secu=
rityRequirements">4.2 Security Requirements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"8b175652b36d">Access to the CloudWatch dashboard must be res=
tricted through <strong>AWS IAM permissions</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9b21826a8672">Only authorized users such as DevOps engineers=
 and administrators should be able to view or modify the dashboard.</p>
<p local-id=3D"e1a451381a49">AWS account security policies must be followed=
.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"226acf86644c">
<h2 local-id=3D"b258730ded6b" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-4.3Usab=
ilityRequirements">4.3 Usability Requirements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"cc6627c1e170">The dashboard should be easy to read and organ=
ized in a clear layout.</p>
<p local-id=3D"073b3466fd7b">Graphs and visualizations should help users qu=
ickly understand infrastructure performance.</p>
<p local-id=3D"3d820c2cf5f9">Metrics should be labeled clearly.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"424c98aa2142">
<h2 local-id=3D"bd182d709f3e" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-4.4Reli=
abilityRequirements">4.4 Reliability Requirements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9f4d01878989">The monitoring system should remain available =
whenever EC2 instances are running.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5420fea50e2a">CloudWatch should reliably collect and display=
 metrics without interruptions.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c7a11a367e36">The dashboard should maintain consistent monit=
oring performance.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"fe923d3423f3">
<h2 local-id=3D"017c214094f8" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-4.5Comp=
lianceRequirements">4.5 Compliance Requirements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"1e54e83a4c5e">The monitoring system must comply with AWS sec=
urity and infrastructure management best practices.</p>
<p local-id=3D"8423e492f1b8">All monitoring activities should follow the or=
ganization's cloud governance policies.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"85c15458b45c">
<h1 local-id=3D"6f8d8b36b571" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-5.Assum=
ptionsandDependencies">5. Assumptions and Dependencies</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"a6c2a9e3b12f" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-5.1Assu=
mptions">5.1 Assumptions</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a780e94cc94f">The following assumptions are made for this pr=
oject:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"de637a49bf0e">
<li local-id=3D"6fd82855dd7d">
<p local-id=3D"e741d83d6fc7">All EC2 instances are running within the AWS a=
ccount</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1e541406f313">
<p local-id=3D"98ffb5545afd">CloudWatch monitoring is enabled</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b7156c56aed6">
<p local-id=3D"2113b9d63ee7">CloudWatch Agent is installed for memory and d=
isk metrics</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7228c0498a88">
<p local-id=3D"c2c3fe7f6817">AWS permissions are available for dashboard cr=
eation</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"2b3d6cac13aa">
<h2 local-id=3D"d92d2406dfbe" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-5.2Depe=
ndencies">5.2 Dependencies</h2>
<p local-id=3D"bc9d0d824092">The project depends on the following:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ac15b933a03c">
<li local-id=3D"e56de5b9e260">
<p local-id=3D"65ed13448df9">AWS EC2 service</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ccaf7a86787a">
<p local-id=3D"2498cd27224d">AWS CloudWatch service</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f7d38896b550">
<p local-id=3D"7971aa4340a9">CloudWatch Agent installation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"57ff116bb583">
<p local-id=3D"a07521061001">AWS Management Console access</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"378f49e0d4bd">
<h1 local-id=3D"e8b1804d107b" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-6.RiskA=
nalysis">6. Risk Analysis</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"3b214648e3a8" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-6.1Risk=
Identification">6.1 Risk Identification</h2>
<p local-id=3D"8b6d0e288118">Potential risks include:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ca98fd5756ef">
<li local-id=3D"f5b110f0a9e6">
<p local-id=3D"966c1bd41823">Missing metrics due to agent misconfiguration<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"69d32c9aa3ce">
<p local-id=3D"340142da6b24">Insufficient IAM permissions</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"abccded0042a">
<p local-id=3D"6f76173b35e0">Dashboard misconfiguration</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"acb04df2e287">
<p local-id=3D"3577c0c43591">Network issues affecting metric collection</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"0fe0dccdbec2">
<h2 local-id=3D"c88371119b02" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-6.2Risk=
Mitigation">6.2 Risk Mitigation</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a8b2e49e950c">To mitigate these risks:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b68ea19effb4">
<li local-id=3D"df6179345907">
<p local-id=3D"5d4408ac2e0c">Ensure CloudWatch Agent is correctly configure=
d</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"78f2a97bab0a">
<p local-id=3D"dd1666e8a9db">Verify IAM permissions before implementation</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"51f3f1b53f9a">
<p local-id=3D"92d313b926cb">Test dashboard widgets after creation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"866199076fcd">
<p local-id=3D"e25cbbb802f0">Monitor EC2 instances to ensure metric collect=
ion is functioning properly</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"6d0dd3cfb306">
<h1 local-id=3D"8cd554155458" id=3D"T10-RequirementAnalysisDocument-7.Gloss=
ary">7. Glossary</h1>
